<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">
<step><![CDATA[Preheat the oven to 170C. Prick the aubergines all over with a fork and place in the oven. Roast for 30 minutes or until very tender.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Place the aubergines in a colander and leave to cool. When the aubergines are cool enough to handle, tear them open and scoop out the flesh with a spoon. Discard the skins and place the flesh in a colander for 20 minutes to allow some of the watery juices to drain.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Warm the olive oil in a large sauté pan over medium heat. Add the tomato paste and cumin and sauté until dark-coloured. Add the shallot and aubergine pulp and continue to sauté until almost dry and very little liquid remains. Blend in a food processor until smooth and add the cold butter. Season well to taste with the salt and pepper.]]></step>
</directions>
